Start playing now Romidar.    The expansions are nice to have, and give you a Huge range of possibilities for hunting locations. <br>
<br>
However, because you are truly old school, and know the old world like the back of you hand (if you think you have forgotten, it should all come back quickly).<br>
<br>
The biggest advantage is a) new spells b) you know good hunting spots, and I fully expect you know all the ins and outs.<br>
<br>
Not to mention that getting upgrades is much simpler than it was in the past.    Yak's are cheap, Bronze is no longer even looted unless you want to sell it to vendors, and levels move a lot quicker than before.  <br>
<br>
With your knowledge of the original 3 expansions, you should be able to fly through the early levels.    Most of the major grouping zones are still there..<br>
<br>
EC - orcs, NK - Bandits, WC - bandits, highkeep and Highpass, Blackburrow, the oasis.   All of them are still happily camped to level quickly, so getting groups won't be a problem.<br>
